Subject&#58; OSG script&#58; cert-renew

Hi,

I&#39;ve just run cert-new to renew a personal certificate.  The trace tells me to ignore the email I get because it is only for web-based cert-renewal, however the email I get says it is for my command line cert request.  Seems like the script should be updated.  A trace of my cert-renew command output is below, along with the email I was sent.

Regards,

Ian

[webportal@portal ~]$ cert-renew
checking CertLib version, V2-7,  This is the latest version, released 18 May 2009.
you will be  prompted for a passphrase to encyrpt the private key that is being generated.
using CA doegrids
Generating a 2048 bit RSA private key
...................+++
....................................................+++
writing new private key to &#39;/home/webportal/.globus/newkey.pem&#39;
Enter PEM pass phrase&#58;
